You are an expert in ontology engineering and legal knowledge representation.

Your task is to construct an OWL ontology in Turtle format from the EU AI Act article chunks provided in JSON.

The ontology should capture the core conceptual structure of the EU AI Act.

Input
You will receive a JSON file containing chunks of EU AI Act articles.

Your task
1. Extract ontology classes representing:
   - AI system categories
   - prohibited AI practices
   - actors (Provider, Deployer, Importer, Distributor, etc.)
   - authorities
   - obligations and requirements
   - regulatory artefacts

2. Extract subclass relations when supported by the text.

3. Create object properties representing relations such as:
   - hasObligation
   - appliesToSystem
   - supervisedBy
   - requiresDocumentation
   - subjectToConformityAssessment

Only create relations when they are grounded in the article text.

4. Annotate every class and property with:
   - rdfs:label
   - skos:definition
   - skos:scopeNote indicating the article number.

5. Follow these modeling principles:
   - Use ontology classes, not individuals.
   - Use PascalCase names for classes.
   - Use camelCase for properties.
   - Do not invent concepts not grounded in the text.
   - Merge duplicate concepts across articles.

6. Output a valid OWL ontology in Turtle syntax.

Use these prefixes:

@prefix : <https://w3id.org/euaiact/ontology#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .

Also include ontology metadata:

dcterms:title "EU AI Act Ontology"@en ;
dcterms:description "A proof-of-concept ontology modelling the key concepts, actors, risk categories, prohibited practices, and obligations defined in Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 — the EU Artificial Intelligence Act."@en ;
dcterms:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=OJ:L_202401689> ;
dcterms:date "2024-07-12"^^xsd:date ;
owl:versionInfo "1.0.0" .


Important constraints

- Output only valid Turtle.
- Do not output explanations.
- Do not output JSON.
- Do not output commentary.

